<h1>@Vte{{}}@HI{{kara}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li><strong>@Vte{{}}@HI{{kara}}</strong>
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<strong>@Vte{{}}@HI{{kara}}</strong> means that the action of the main sentence
takes place (or took place) after the subordinate clause. So the meaning might
be rendered as "after X, " or "since X, " where X is the subordinate clause.

<p></p>


<h2> Examples </h2>

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{@KJ{{exertion^strong}}ga @KJ{{end}}wa<strong>tte kara</strong>, @KT{{tenisu}}wo shimashou.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    Let's play tennis after we've finished studying.
  </td> </tr>
</table>

<h2> Notes </h2>

<strong>@HI{{kara}}</strong> can be omitted if the main verb does not have a high degree of volition
on the part of the speaker.
